📋 COSTAR Framework Application

🔵 C — Context

A 200-bed private multi-speciality hospital in Telangana, India, requires a fully integrated Digital Health Platform that works both online and offline. The hospital serves Telugu and English-speaking patients. It needs AI agents spanning clinical care, diagnostics, wellness, nutrition, physiotherapy, yoga, software engineering (self-healing), and hardware monitoring — all unified under a single platform deployed on GitHub for free, collaborative development.

🎯 O — Objective

Build and deploy a world-class, AI-powered hospital management and patient care system that:


Manages all hospital operations (OPD, IPD, OT, ICU, pharmacy, billing)
Supports Telugu & English voice interactions for patients and staff
Integrates AI agents for every clinical and non-clinical domain
Works completely offline (local LLM + edge AI) and syncs when online
Includes AI-powered software self-healing and hardware fault detection
Is free to deploy using open-source tools hosted on GitHub


📝 S — Steps (Breakdown of Tasks)


Set up GitHub repository structure and CI/CD pipeline
Build the core Hospital Management System (HMS)
Integrate all AI clinical agents
Implement Telugu + English voice agents
Build offline-first architecture with sync
Add physiotherapy, yoga, dietician AI modules
Integrate AI Software Engineer & Hardware Engineer agents
Deploy and document


🛠️ T — Tools / Stack


Frontend: React.js + PWA (offline support)
Backend: FastAPI (Python) + Node.js
Database: PostgreSQL (online) + SQLite (offline) + Sync Engine
AI/LLM: Ollama (local/offline) + Anthropic Claude API (online)
Voice: Mozilla TTS + Whisper STL (Telugu/English), offline-capable
Hardware Monitoring: Python sensors + OpenCV + AlertManager
DevOps: GitHub Actions + Docker + Docker Compose
Deployment: GitHub Pages (frontend) + Railway/Render (backend) — Free tier


⚙️ A — Actions / Output Format


Structured GitHub repository with all modules
Documented APIs, agent configurations, and workflows
Bilingual UI (Telugu / English)
Automated CI/CD pipeline for testing and deployment


🔁 R — Reflection / Iteration Loop


AI Software Engineer Agent monitors logs → detects bugs → auto-patches → creates GitHub PR
AI Hardware Engineer Agent monitors sensors → displays fault location on screen → alerts technician
Nightly health checks run automated regression suites
Patient outcome feedback loops improve clinical AI agents monthly



